  "root_cause_assessment": "Junk sources are NOT the primary cause of the win rate drop \u2014 they were present from day 1 with no sudden increase. Primary factors: (1) horse racing signals appearing in W25 with no model calibration; (2) 43% of trades have no model probability recorded (claude_prob_pct=0), dragging WR; (3) tournament concentration risk (7/15 W24 losses on Canadian Open); (4) pre-fix BUG-145 duplicate bets; (5) small sample size makes WR volatile. Fix BUG-148 (junk domain blocklist) anyway as hygiene \u2014 it prevents future junk-only briefs \u2014 but expect the WR fix to come from (1) and (2).",
  "conclusion": "Junk sources have been ~20% of Tavily results since day 1 and correlate with NOTHING in the win rate data. The W24-W25 drop is real but driven by horse racing entering the model (new unmodelled sport), missing model probabilities on 43% of live trades, and a 7-loss concentration on the Canadian Open. Fix the domain blocklist as hygiene but do not expect it to recover the win rate alone."
